instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The twin feeds control commands back to the crane: the Trajectory Generator Service produces optimal trajectories, which the Control Application translates into motor step commands and sends to the motor drivers. The Continuous Validation Service triggers operator notifications via the dashboard if deviations exceed thresholds. These commands are transmitted over MQTT to the Arduino‑based interface."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "Data is exchanged in near‑real‑time with a sampling interval of a few milliseconds for sensor uploads, while trajectory planning and validation operate at higher (1–5 s) intervals. The twin therefore operates at real‑time/ near‑real‑time synchronization with the physical system."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The twin constellation consists of the physical‑crane interface, control application, logging application on the physical side; on the virtual side, the database, dashboard, trajectory generator, simulation, continuous validation, and MQTT broker, all orchestrated via docker‑compose and interconnected through an MQTT network."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The twin covers all phases of the system's life‑cycle: design (CAD and kinematic model), manufacturing (assembly of the physical crane), operation (runtime monitoring, control, and validation), and maintenance (periodic updates of the twin services)."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Fidelity ensured by detailed kinematic and dynamic models; validity continuously checked by comparing real measurements to simulation outputs. Deviations beyond a defined threshold trigger alerts. Model uncertainties, sensor noise, and unmodeled disturbances are acknowledged and handled by the validation service."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "Communication between PT and DT uses an MQTT broker (Eclipse Mosquitto) running locally on the same host or network. The Arduino controller publishes sensor data to MQTT topics and subscribes to command topics; the Python interface translates between hardware and MQTT. The Docker containers connect over a Docker network, and the physical interface may use USB/serial to the Arduino."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "All twin services are containerized and deployed on a single compute node (e.g., a personal computer) using Docker Compose. The database, broker, and dashboard are separate containers, while the application logic resides in dedicated containers. The process is automatically bootstrapped by the compose file, which initializes the database schema and Grafana dashboards."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "While not directly integrated in the exemplar, the authors mention potential extensions to link the crane twin to a ship and harbor simulation, suggesting that integration with other DTs or external systems could be achieved in future work."
]
